<HEADLINE> U.N. Welcomes Upcoming Sierra Leonean Gov't-Rebels Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Security Council Friday welcomed the upcoming negotiations between
the government of Sierra Leone and the rebels.
</P>
<P>
The move came after the Security Council was briefed Friday
morning by the Secretariat on the latest developments in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The Council praised the presence and action by the Economic
Community of West African States (ECOWAS) on the ground.
</P>
<P>
The Council recalled the need for international support for the
ECOWAS Military Observer Group (ECOMOG) and other international
agencies providing humanitarian aid.
</P>
<P>
The Council expressed its concern over the humanitarian
situation in the country and reports of armed supplies to the
rebels.
</P>
<P>
The talks will take place in Togo upon the initiative by
President Gnassingbe Eyadema of this country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
