<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1 SLA Militiaman Killed, 4 Wounded in S. Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, April 23 (Xinhua) -- A member of the pro-Israeli South
Lebanon Army (SLA) militia was killed and four others were wounded
Friday night by a roadside bomb in south Lebanon, the Voice of the
People radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The injured included a high ranking SLA official who was in
serious condition and has been transported to Israel for
treatment.
</P>
<P>
The casualties were caused when a bomb exploded near the
convoy of those militiamen on a road in Jezzine, north of the
Israeli occupied border zone in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
In Beirut, the Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God,
claimed responsibility for the bombing.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a self-styled security zone in south Lebanon in
1985 with the claimed aim of protecting its north from Lebanese
guerrillas' cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Lebanon's resistance movement spearheaded by
Hezbollah has been fighting to drive Israeli forces out of the
country.
</P>
<P>
The bombing followed an Israeli bombardment Friday afternoon
on a village just outside the zone, which wounded three Lebanese
civilians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
