<HEADLINE> Moderate Quake Jolts Nicaragua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- A 4.4 degree in the Richter scale
earthquake shook Nicaragua Friday morning, the Territorial Studies
Nicaraguan Institute (INETER) told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The tremor occurred at 04:18 local time and its epicenter was
located 141 kilometers southwest of Managua.
</P>
<P>
The seism epicenter was in the Pacific Ocean, across from La
Boquita and Casares, at a depth of eight kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The phenomenon was caused by the movements between the Cocos
and Caribbean tectonic plates, said the INETER. 
</P>
</TEXT>
