<HEADLINE> Hundreds of S. African Miners Trapped Underground </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Almost all the miners, who
were trapped underground in Welkom, about 300 km southwest of
Johannesburg after an earthquake Friday morning, have been brought
safely to the surface, South African Broadcasting Corporation
reported.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted a spokeswoman for the Anglogold Company as
saying that about 1,000 miners working for Anglogold Company were
trapped when the tremor took place early in the morning.
</P>
<P>
Rescuers said that so far two men who were trapped at about
1,300 meters below surface, have not been found. Their destiny is
not known yet.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the authorities had to bring emergency
power generators after electricity and water facilities in the
whole area were destroyed by the tremor.
</P>
<P>
Anglogold's operations at the site have been stopped and
production is expected to resume on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
