following a meeting of the RCD leadership, the governors of the
provinces which fell to the rebels during the eight-month old
war.
</P>
<P>
The RCD has embarked on a program of sensitizing the local
Congolese, notably the Mai Mai tribal militia to dissociate
themselves from the guerrilla forces operating in the region. It
has also deployed police units in over 70 territories of the
provinces it conquered.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Congolese rebels have blasted the peace deal signed
by Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni and Laurent Kabila, alleging
 that they had not been associated. 
