<HEADLINE> Army Worms Invade Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Army worms, a kind of injurious
insects to crops, are plaguing in many parts of Rwanda and it may
cause serious havoc in the African country, official sources said
in Kigali, Rwandan capital.
</P>
<P>
The Rwandan Minister of Agriculture, Animal Resources and
Forestry Ephrem Kabayija, said that the army worms multiplies
very quickly and spread fast with the wind, if they are not
immediately stopped, this could cause serious havoc in the
country.
</P>
<P>
According to Rwandan News Agency report, the worms have
ravaged three sectors of communes Rwisirabo in Umutara, Rilima in
Kigali Rural, Rukira and Nyarubuye in Kibungo.
</P>
<P>
Minister Kabaija called upon anyone who identifies the army
worms to report immediately to local authorities.
</P>
<P>
He said that his department can provide pesticides for about
10,000 hectares, if it is not enough, the ministry can order for
more.
</P>
<P>
The minister also called for the immediate assistance from the
armed forces to fight the insects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
