<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Oceanographer Says La Nina Will End This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese oceanographers agree that
the weather phenomenon of La Nina will end in the latter half of
this year.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese State Oceanic Administration revealed this
conclusion in a news conference held today. Experts believe that
La Nina has passed its peak and will continuously decrease.
</P>
<P>
La Nina's literal meaning is 'girl' and is brought about by
colder than normal surface temperatures in the Pacific Ocean which
greatly affects global weather patterns as much as its rival El
Nino.
</P>
<P>
The latest La Nina emerged last summer and is believed to have
had some effect on the great floods along China's Yangtze River
last summer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
