<HEADLINE> Marine Disasters More Serious Than Last Year, Experts Predict </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Oceanographers have
agreed that China's marine disasters in 1999 will be more serious
than last year.
</P>
<P>
Experts predict that the frequent occurrences of disastrous
storms along coastal areas will be higher than last year and the
level of the disasters will also be more serious.
</P>
<P>
There were only three disastrous storms in China in 1998,
considerably down on ten years ago, according to experts.
</P>
<P>
However, there will be four or five disastrous storms along
China's coastal areas between June and October and maybe one or
two between September and October, experts predict.
</P>
<P>
The State Oceanic Administration has required local governments
in coastal areas to be alert to these upcoming disasters and
reduce losses to a minimum.
</P>
<P>
Marine disasters caused direct economic loss to China of about
1 billion yuan last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
