<HEADLINE> EDS-Details Added Anti-China Resolution Doomed to Fail, FM Spokesman (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The United States was merely
playing "an anti-China melodrama" when proposing an anti-China
resolution on human rights and its move was doomed to fail, said
China's Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi here tonight.
</P>
<P>
Sun made the remarks after the adoption of a decision not to
review and vote on the U.S.-sponsored draft resolution on China's
human rights situation at the 55th session of the United Nations
Commission on Human Rights held in Geneva, Switzerland, this
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The UN commission voted in favor of a Chinese proposal to take
no action on the U.S. resolution with 22 votes in favor, 17
against and 14 in abstention at the session, according to the
latest report.
</P>
<P>
It was the eighth time that the United Nations Commission on
Human Rights turned down an anti-China resolution since 1990.
</P>
<P>
Sun expressed his admiration and gratitude to all the countries
that have upheld justice and rendered support to China in foiling
the resolution.
</P>
<P>
Sun described the U.S. as being in a "solitary position," when
tabling the resolution, saying the move would firmly be opposed by
China and a large number of developing countries. Even the
European Union and some western countries had not joined the U.S.
efforts this year, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
