<HEADLINE> Six Hurt in Police Chase Shooting in England </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Six people were hurt Friday after
gunmen opened fire in Greater Manchester in middle England after a
failed robbery attempt.
</P>
<P>
Police said four people had been arrested at the end of a
"major incident" which began in Lancashire, according to a BBC
report.
</P>
<P>
The gang, who are believed to have carried out a failed robbery
in Chorley, Lancashire, abandoned their car in Bolton, Greater
Manchester, around lunch time.
</P>
<P>
They then hijacked a silver BMW car to Rochdale, 190 miles (305
km) northwest of London, where six people were injured in three
separate shootings.
</P>
<P>
At one point the gunmen, with several police Range Rovers in
pursuit, shot at a queue of people at a bus stop, hitting one man
in the head.
</P>
<P>
The gang were followed by police and the silver BMW car crashed
near Rochdale Town Hall, with two arrested on the spot.
</P>
<P>
A Kalashnikov AK-47 assault rifle and a pistol were later
recovered from the BMW.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Rochdale Infirmary said they were dealing with
five casualties -- one person had an arm injury, two had leg
wounds, one was suffering from severe shock and a fifth suffered
chest pains after being shot at. 
</P>
</TEXT>
