<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Both Thailand and China are ready
to work together to promote cooperation whether it is of
bilateral, multilateral or international level, Thai Prime
Minister Chuan Leekpai said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark during an interview with Chinese reporters
two days before he starts a visit to South Korea and China.
</P>
<P>
He said that as the 21st century is approaching, China and
Thailand has signed the Joint statement on a Plan of Action for
the 21st Century, which is the first agreement of its kind between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
