<HEADLINE> France Intercepts Yugoslav Registered Civilian Aircraft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 23 (Xinhua) -- A French Mirage warplane
intercepted Thursday in French air space a Yugoslav registered
civilian aircraft rented by a Greek company, said the official
Direction Generale de L'Aviation Civil (DGAC) Friday.
</P>
<P>
A Dutch made Fokker aircraft registered in Montenegro was
intercepted during its flight from Athens to Lyon with 75
passengers on board, said the DGAC.
</P>
<P>
The plane, rented by the Greek tourism company Princess, was
forced to land in Lyon after being intercepted, said officials.
</P>
<P>
The plane left Lyon Friday morning for Athens, and all its
passengers, most of them French from the region of Lyon on a trip
organized by an unidentified company, left the plane in a normal
way, they added.
</P>
<P>
The Montenegran newspaper Vijesti said Friday that two French
Mirage warplanes intercepted the Fokker because it carried the
inscription "YU."
</P>
<P>
The plane was flying to Paris, instead of Lyon, said the
newspaper. 
</P>
