<HEADLINE> Thai PM Thanks China for Purchasing Farm Produce </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Thai Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai
on Friday thanked China for purchasing agricultural products from
his country which faces difficulties.
</P>
<P>
This is not simply a trade matter and it reflects China's firm
friendship toward Thailand, Chuan said in an interview with
Chinese reporters in Bangkok two days before he starts a visit to
South Korea and China.
</P>
<P>
"This is something which Thai farmers and the Thai government
will always acknowledge," he said.
</P>
<P>
China has recently agreed to purchase 200,000 tons of rice,
100,000 tons of rubber and 200,000 tons of tapioca from Thailand.
</P>
<P>
As for economic cooperation between the two countries, Chuan
said what is important to economic cooperation is trade and
investment, in which bilateral cooperation has progressed well.
</P>
<P>
"Since the day we established diplomatic relations, the number
of Thai projects invested in China has increased from one to one
thousand. I believe further expansion will be seen in the
increasing cooperation in the field of investment," he said.
</P>
<P>
Chuan said the trade volume between Thailand and China has
continued to increase over the years, which shows the potential
for trade between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Since the economic crisis began to hit the region, China has
been playing an important role in maintaining and promoting
stability of the region by not devaluating its currency, he added.
</P>
<P>
Chuan said he believed there will be more areas of trade in
which the two countries can increase cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Chuan is expected to leave on Sunday for Seoul for a three-day
visit to South Korea before going to Shanghai next Wednesday to
start a six-day official visit to China. 
</P>
