<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2100 GMT, April 23 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- A liver donated by the family of a 37-year-old
Palestinian man has been divided into two and transplanted into
the bodies of two Israeli patients, according to a report obtained
here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time in Israel that a donated liver was
split for two recipients, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Six internal organs from the Palestinian man who was from the
West Bank, including his heart, kidney and a liver, were
transplanted into four different patients at an Israeli hospital
last Tuesday. (BC-Israel-Liver-Split)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli police are investigating a death threat
against Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and his family, Israel
Radio reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman confirmed a Maariv newspaper report Friday
that a letter sent to Netanyahu's office warned him to withdraw
his candidacy for prime ministership in the May elections and
threatened to kill him and his family if he wins.
</P>
<P>
An automatic rifle bullet was included in the envelop
containing the threat letter, Maariv said. (BC-Israel-Elections)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- A member of the pro-Israeli South Lebanon Army (SLA)
militia was killed and four others were wounded Friday night by a
roadside bomb in south Lebanon, the Voice of the People radio
reported.
</P>
<P>
The injured included a high ranking SLA official who was in
serious condition and has been transported to Israel for
treatment. (BC-Lebanon-SLA-Wounded)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkish Prime Minister Bulent Ecevit said Friday that
Turkey will take necessary measures to prevent possible threat
from the deployment of Russian-made missiles on a Greek island.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks after Greece confirmed Thursday that a
Russian-made S-300 anti-aircraft system, which was originally
destined for Cyprus, has begun being assembled on the Greek island.
(BC-Turkey-Greece) 
