<HEADLINE> Weak Wall St. Start Weakens Europe Except London </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON April 23 (Xinhua) - Weak opening on Wall Street sent
leaeding European markets to close mainly lower Friday despite
gains on telecommunication stocks boosted by hopes of further
mega-mergers in the sector.
</P>
<P>
UK blue chips were left with light gains at the close, as
positive sentiment from Wall Street's record close the day before
evaporated throughout the session.
</P>
<P>
An early bout of profit-taking on Wall Street accentuated the
drift, although the FTSE 100 did not appear in danger of slipping
into the red.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE 100 index closed 14.4 points higher at 6428.0, a gain
of 0.2 percent. The index remained in the black for the whole
session and saw a 6469.2 session high at 9.16am.
</P>
<P>
Frankfurt's electronically-traded Xetra Dax failed to maintain
its grasp on early gains amid morning weakness on Wall Street. The
index ended down 0.74 percent at 5187.89. The Dax was up 0.8
percent for the week.
</P>
<P>
In Paris shares were also in the red as slim gains on opening
were erased. The CAC index of leading shares was down 29.42 points
at 4262.43. 
</P>
