<HEADLINE> Four People Killed in Plane Crash in Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Another person died in hospital,
bringing the death toll to four in a civilian plane crash in
Israel Saturday morning, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft, which belongs to a sky diving school, crashed in
a hillside near a cooperative farm near the northern port city of
Haifa, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
Ten people were aboard the plane, one pilot and nine sky
divers. The six injured are being treated in hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigation found that there might be a mechanical
malfunction in the plane, according to the radio reports.
</P>
<P>
Before the crash, the plane diverted from its planned course
and it appeared that the pilot had attempted to make an emergency
landing on a coastal highway.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman at the diving school was quoted by the radio as
saying that the pilot is a veteran airman and the Swiss-made plane
was well-maintained and had been checked before the flight
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said there is no black box in the plane. 
</P>
