<HEADLINE> China Deals Harshly with Abuse of Treasury Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Finance (MOF) and
the State Development Planning Commission (SDPC) are to stop
allocating any more treasury funds to east China's Jiangxi
Province because of alleged misuse of such funds.
</P>
<P>
During a recent investigation, the MOF discovered that a number
of regions in Jiangxi have defrauded the central government by
establishing projects which exist in name only.
</P>
<P>
Some regions have also diverted funds earmarked for special
projects without permission from the central government. In
addition, fake accounts and contracts were drawn up in order to
conceal the truth.
</P>
<P>
The MOF and SDPC decided to halt the allocation of funds for
projects apart from water conservancy and others that have high
level approval until these issues are cleared up.
</P>
<P>
They have urged the provincial government to severely punish
officials involved in the scams.
</P>
<P>
They have also demanded all other regions in the country learn
a lesson from these cases and strengthen their management and
supervision of state funds.
</P>
<P>
Authorities in Jiangxi province are currently investigating the
cases and will be recommending action. 
</P>
</TEXT>
