<DOCNO> XIE19990424.0074 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt Supports Political Settlement for Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr
Moussa said on Saturday that his country supports political
settlement for the Kosovo crisis in Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
After a meeting between President Hosni Mubarak and visiting
Russian Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov, Moussa told reporters that
Egypt and Russia share stances on the Kosovo issue.
</P>
<P>
"We are all interested in a political settlement, the need to
respect the (Yugoslav) sovereignty and territorial integrity and
reject any policy of ethnic cleansing or the violation of the
basic rights of the people of Kosovo," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Kosovar refugees must safely return to their homes within
an acceptable formula in accordance with international law, he
added.
</P>
<P>
NATO has been bombing Yugoslav targets since March 24 to force
Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic to accept a peace plan
which will allow the alliance to deploy troops in the southern
Serbian province of Kosovo as peacekeepers.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of thousands of ethnic Albanians have fled Kosovo to
neighboring Albania and Macedonia after NATO launched the
airstrikes.
</P>
<P>
During the hour-long talks, Mubarak also discussed with Ivanov
the latest developments in the Middle East peace process and ways
of promoting bilateral ties, Moussa said.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov arrived in Cairo Friday evening within a regional tour,
which has taken him to Israel and the Palestinian self-rule
areas. He will then travel to Syria and Lebanon after wrapping up
visit here.
</P>
<P>
"We have exchanged views on international issues and our
bilateral relations and the talks have clearly shown that Egypt
and Russia are linked in many ways," said the Russian minister.
</P>
<P>
"We build our relations on the agreements reached in 1997
during President Mubarak's visit in Moscow and the talks he held
with (Russian) President (Boris) Yeltsin," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Russian minister added that he briefed Mubarak on his
country's efforts to defuse the crisis in the Balkans.
</P>
<P>
He called on all parties to show political determination to
reach a political settlement for the Kosovo crisis, saying that
Russia will exert efforts with other countries to seek a
solution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
