<HEADLINE> Pacquiao Stops Mexican Challenger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- World Boxing Council (WBC)
flyweight champion Manny Pacquiao of the Philippines retianed his
crown by flooring Mexican Gabriel Mira five times before knocking
him out in the fourth round on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old challenger was on his knees, his face on the
canvas, when American referee Richard Steele signalled the end of
the 12-round contest after the Mexican went down for the third
time in the round, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Mira tried to fight back, jarring Pacquiao with rights to the
head, but the Filipino repulsed the Mexican's desperate attack
with wicked left hooks and uppercuts before finishing him off.
</P>
<P>
Under the WBC's three-knockdown rule, the fight result is
listed as a knockout. 
</P>
