Saturday in Washington that the agreement, reached by President
Jacques Chirac and President Bill Clinton Friday night, is not far
from the last (NATO) strategic concept of 1991, which stresses
that the alliance should act in conformity with U.N. principles.
(France-U.S.-Agreement France) 
