<HEADLINE> Rheumatoid Symposium Held in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SHANGHAI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China's first symposium on
rheumatoid diseases was held here today.
</P>
<P>
Some 300 experts from the Chinese mainland, Hong Kong and
Taiwan participated and submitted 320 papers to the symposium.
</P>
<P>
There are over 100 kinds of rheumatoid disease and about 10
percent of the world's population are affected.
</P>
<P>
With the improvement of life in China, the pattern of the
disease has undergone some changes, experts told the symposium.
</P>
<P>
The number of rheumatoid arthritis and Cazenave's lupus
patients went down, while those affected by ostarthritis and gout
increased.
</P>
<P>
At present, about 13 percent of the Chinese population is
plagued by ostarthritis, the experts said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
