<HEADLINE> World's Oldest Giant Panda Celebrates 37th Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The world's oldest giant panda,
called Dudu, spent "her" 37th birthday happily today in Wuhan Zoo
in central China.
</P>
<P>
Over ten children attended Dudu's birthday party and expressed
the wish that she will enter the new millennium with them.
</P>
<P>
Born in 1962, Dudu was first transferred to Chengdu Zoo and
then moved to Wuhan in 1972. She is in fair health although she
sometimes affected by diseases caused by old age.
</P>
<P>
China now has less than 1,200 giant pandas. The average life
span of wild giant pandas is around 15 years while that of pandas
in captivity is around 25 years.  
</P>
