<HEADLINE> France, U.S. Reach Agreement on Legality of Future NATO Actions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 24 (Xinhua) -- France and the United States have
reached an agreement that future NATO actions should be performed
in conformity with the principles of the United Nations, according
to a report by Agence France-Presse (AFP) on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The AFP quoted unidentified U.S. and NATO sources as saying on
Saturday in Washington that the agreement, reached by President
Jacques Chirac and President Bill Clinton Friday night, is not far
from the last (NATO) strategic concept of 1991, which stresses
that the alliance should act in conformity with U.N. principles.
</P>
<P>
The 1991 NATO strategic concept says that it is the "
fundamental tasks" of NATO to "safeguard the freedom and security
of all its members by political and military means, in conformity
with the principles of the Charter of the United Nations."
</P>
<P>
No further details about the agreement can be obtained
immediately, said the AFP.
</P>
<P>
The NATO Washington summit, which opened on Friday, is expected
to adopt a new strategic concept. 
</P>
</TEXT>
