<HEADLINE> Mubarak Terms Peace as Right Choice in Mideast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak on
Saturday reiterated that choice of peace is the right way to solve
problems in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
In a televised speech marking Israel's 1982 return of Sinai to
Egypt, Mubarak said that "most certainly, just peace is the right
option, or rather the only one, which all peoples in the region,
including the Israelis, side with."
</P>
<P>
He called on Arabs and Israelis to set aside their differences
and work toward realizing the Mideast peace.
</P>
<P>
"The peace march will not be derailed no matter what hurdles it
faces," said Mubarak, calling for a "historic reconciliation"
between the Arabs and the Israelis to end their conflict.
</P>
<P>
"Those who call for war are a minority who have strayed from
the path of peace, and their fate is that they will be forgotten,
no matter how loud their voices are," he underlined.
</P>
<P>
Peace talks between the Palestinians and Israel have faltered
repeatedly since Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu took
office in May 1996. The two sides have argued over numerous
issues, including security for Israel and Palestinian statehood.
</P>
<P>
Egypt was the first Arab country to sign a peace treaty with
Israel. The 1979 Camp David accords paved the way for the return
of Sinai to Egypt, which was captured by Israel during the 1967
Arab-Israeli war. 
</P>
</TEXT>
