<HEADLINE> Young Scientific Workers Gather to Mark May 4th Movement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,000 young scientific
workers and college students gathered in Beijing today to listen
to a public lecture, which was held to mark the 80th anniversary
of the May Fourth Movement.
</P>
<P>
Five outstanding scientific and medical workers gave speeches
to the young audience to highlight "patriotism, progress,
democracy and science", which is the tradition of the movement.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the speeches will give more incentive to young
people so that they will contribute to the great course of
'revitalizing the country through science and education'", said Lu
Yongxiang, president of the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS).
</P>
<P>
He said that the younger generation in modern China has the
greatest power for boosting knowledge and that many young
scientific workers have already become the backbone of the
country's scientific progress.
</P>
<P>
He urged young people to play a more active role in the
country's knowledge innovation projects.
</P>
<P>
The public lecture was jointly sponsored by the CAS, the
Central Committee of the Communist Youth League of China and the
China Central Television Station.  
</P>
