<HEADLINE> Higgins Cruises into Last Eight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Reigning champion John Higgins of
Scotland breezed into the last eight of the World Championship in
Sheffield, England, on Saturday, by beating English left-hander
Mark King 13-4,
</P>
<P>
Higgins, 23, reached the last eight dropping only six frames
and capturing 23.
</P>
<P>
In contrast, John Parrott, the first player into the last eight,
struggled for 10 hours 17 minutes to deny another Scot, Chris
Small, 13-12 on Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Malta's Tony Drago halved his overnight four-frame deficit
helped by breaks of 108 and 137 against Welshman Matthew Stevens.
Drago was 7-5 down in a match concluding later on Saturday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
