<HEADLINE> Qinghua University Re-establishes Law School </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Qinghua University today
announced the re-establishment of its Law School, which was closed
47 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Qinghua University President Wan Dazhong called it "a
significant event in Qinghua's history".
</P>
<P>
"Legal construction is very important for China's socialist
modernization process, and the Qinghua Law School will nurture
excellent legal talents for China," said Wang.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the re-establishment of the Law School is a
crucial step in Qinghua's efforts to transform itself into a first-
class university in the world.
</P>
<P>
The 88-year-old Qinghua University set up its Law School in
1928, and it was incorporated within other universities in 1952.
</P>
<P>
Luo Haocai, vice-Chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National Committee, and over 300
officials and students from Qinghua University and ministries of
Education, Justice and Public Security attended today's ceremony.
</P>
