<HEADLINE> Interrupted Xinjiang Railways Resume Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Lanzhou-Xinjiang railway and
the line crossing south Xinjiang were reopened gradually around
noon today after being closed by strong winds and heavy snow.
</P>
<P>
 The bad weather, which has hit most parts of China's Xinjiang
Uygur Autonomous Region since Thursday, brought interruptions to
railway operations in the vast region.
</P>
<P>
 Some sections on the Lanzhou-Xinjiang railway were hit by a
hurricane, which battered passenger trains and broke their windows.
</P>
<P>
 Three passenger trains in southern Xinjiang were stranded and
railway timetables in the region's north were also interrupted.
</P>
<P>
 At present, nearly a thousand railway workers are still
fighting against the clock to repair the damaged facilities.
