<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government has thus
far inspected 3,120 business establishments and acted upon 97
anti-pollution cases, in keeping with its intensified campaign
against pollution and other nemesis of the environment.
</P>
<P>
A recently released report of the Environment and Natural
Resources Department also said that fifty-one air quality sampling
stations have been set up from the time President Joseph Estrada
took over on June 30, 1998.
</P>
