one of his administration's top concerns in his first
State-of-the-Nation Address before Congress in July last year.
</P>
<P>
The president has directed the country's concerned agencies to
attack air and water pollution as well as garbage, traffic and
squatting problems, in line with his vow in the May 1998
presidential campaign to address these urban woes. 
