<HEADLINE> Angola's Around-Africa Walker Hospitalized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Lucio dos Santos Feirreira, an
Angolan who is about to finish his five-year-long around-Africa
travel on foot was admitted into hospital in Chimoio City in
central Mozambique's Manica Province.
</P>
<P>
He was admitted into the city hospital a week ago for malaria,
rheumatism after experiencing numerous setbacks, including robbery
by a group of armed bandits who took away his communication set.
</P>
<P>
The Angola Daily reported that Feirreira, who started the
adventure from South Africa in January 1994, aiming to enter
Guinness Book with the long walk.
</P>
<P>
He started his walk from western coast of the continent in
South Africa, heading northward and returned from the eastern
coast.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old Angolan said he will recover soon and continue
his trip to Maputo, capital of Mozambique and try to win
Mozambican President Joaquim Chissano's help.
</P>
<P>
Feirreira has got help from Angolan government and some U.S.
companies at the start of his adventure. He plans to reach South
Africa early next year to his starting point in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
