<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Military Chopper Crashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- An Indonesian military chopper
crashed into a paddy field in Kertasari village in the West Javan
district of Ciamis on Saturday morning, wounding 10 people on
board.
</P>
<P>
All passengers of the chopper, taking off from the West Javan
city of Bandung, were seriously or lightly wounded, according to
Antara News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Shortly after the chopper flew into Ciamis sky, it suddenly
became destabilized and spiraled downwards in rotation before
crashing into the paddy field.
</P>
<P>
Quoting witnesses, Ciamis police said before the helicopter
crashed from about 20 meters high, it lost its rear propeller,
leading to an unstable condition.
</P>
<P>
On the cause of the accident, Ciamis police said air force
officials are still doing the investigation. 
</P>
