<HEADLINE>   Philippines' Decade-old National Archery Mark Broken </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Archer Jennifer Chan displayed her
accuracy to establish a new national record in the single 60-meter
event at the 1st Qualifying Tournament at the University of the
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Chan, a member of the women's national team that bagged a gold
medal in the 1997 Jakarta Southeast Asian Games, garnered a 322
total points to erase an old record of 330 points set by Joan
Tabanag in 1989.
</P>
<P>
The lady bow and arrow specialist from the Silliman U--
Dumaguete Archery Club also topped the women's division with a
score of 103 points. Purita Joy Marino came in second with 102
points.
</P>
<P>
Adelinda Figueroa, a 15-year-old girl from Tondo, Manila that
made a rare victory in the US Archery Open Championships, finished
third with 96 points.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Oscar Briones of the Araullo Archery Club, on the
other hand, dominated the men's division with 106 points.
</P>
<P>
Two more qualifying tournaments will be conducted as part of
Philippines' preparation for the 40th World Archery Championships
to be held in Riom, France on July 19-29 and the Asian Archery
Championship in Beijing slated for August 29- September 6.
</P>
<P>
The next qualifying competition will be held on May 22-25 and
the last one will be June 4-7. 
</P>
</TEXT>
