<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fresh Fighting Kills 10 Tamil Rebels in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Friday killed 10 Tamil rebels in separate clashes with the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) guerrillas in the north of
the country, the Defense Ministry said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Troops observed rebel movement and engaged with small arms and
machine guns, killing five rebels at Tadduvankoddi in Jaffna, the
ministry said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
The release said troops killed four LTTE rebels southeast of
Periyamadu in the Wanni area when they attacked a rebel bunker
line with machine guns and small arms.
</P>
<P>
Government troops sniped and killed another rebel north of
Mankulam, also in the Wanni area.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a separatist war against the Sri
Lankan government since 1983 for an independent Tamil homeland in
the north and east of the country. 
</P>
