<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: ABCs of Macao SAR Basic Law (50) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Following is part 50 of a
question and answer series on the Basic Law of the Macao Special
Administrative Region (MSAR).
</P>
<P>
Will the Government of the Macao Special Administrative Region
protect the scenic spots and historical sites in Macao?
</P>
<P>
The infusion of the Chinese and Western cultures has left many
unique sites of historical interest, scenic spots and other
tourist attractions in Macao, such as the serene and picturesque
Temple of the Goddess A-Ma, the grand and imposing St. Paul's
Facade, the interconnected Puji Peaceful Seclusion for meditation,
the Dong Wang Yang Soughing Lighthouse, the fascinating Luyuan
Garden with winding corridors, and the Dragon Ring Exhibition of
houses of the unique Portuguese Style.
</P>
<P>
They are not only the testimony to the cultural heritage of
Macao, but also famous tourist attractions. Article 125 of the
Basic Law provides that after the return of Macao, the Government
of the Macao Special Administrative Region shall protect by law
scenic spots, historical sites and other historical relics as well
as the lawful rights and interests of the owners of antiques. (
More)
nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
