<HEADLINE> Knicks Halt Charlotte's Winning Streak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Patrick Ewing and Allan
Houston combined their efforts for 56 points to lead the New York
Knicks for a 110-105 victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Houston scored a season-high 30 points and Ewing added 26 to
halt Charlotte's nine-game winning streak in their first game
after Ernie Grunfeld was fired on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
New York, losers of its four previous games, overtook the
Hornets into a tie for eighth place with Toronto for the last
playoff spot in the East Conference.
</P>
<P>
The Knicks took an 18-point lead in the third quarter before
the Hornets closed within one late in the fourth quarter.
</P>
<P>
At Orlando, Vince Carter scored 24 points to pace the Raptors
for a 95-88 win over the Magic as Toronto made 11 3-pointers for
their third straight road win.
</P>
<P>
Orlando fell 1 1/2 games behind first-place Miami in the battle
for best record in the East.
</P>
<P>
Reserve Dee Brown scored 18 points for Toronto, including 4-of-
9 on 3-pointers.
</P>
<P>
At Washington, Steve Smith scored 20 points and Mookie Blaylock
had 17 points and 10 assists as the Atlanta Hawks won their fifth
straight by beating the Wizards 89-78.
</P>
<P>
Atlanta tied its longest winning streak of the season to rank
in the fourth place in the Eastern Conference with six games left.
</P>
<P>
The Chicago Bulls were toppled by the Boston Celtics 71-100 as
Paul Pierce scored 18 points and Ron Mercer added 13 to snap the
Celtics' three-game losing streak.
</P>
<P>
At Milwaukee, Glenn Robinson had 26 points and 17 rebounds as
the Bucks handed Cleveland its fourth straight loss 79-75 when
Shawn Kemp was out with a sprained left foot.
</P>
<P>
The Cavaliers fell a game behind New York and Toronto for the
last playoff spot in the East.
</P>
<P>
In other games, Denver Nuggets routed the Golden State Warriors
96-84 in their first game in five games due to a school shooting,
LA Clippers toppled Houston Rockets 106-101, Sacremento Kings
outscored Minnesota 105-97, Utah Jazz defeated Portland 96-85, and
Seattle bt Vancouver 97-84. 
</P>
</TEXT>
