<HEADLINE> Manila to Ban Importation of Luxury Cars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' Department of
Finance (DOF) vowed to ban the importation of luxury vehicles by
foreign consultants hired by the Philippine government for its
various infrastructure projects in the country.
</P>
<P>
Finance Secretary Edgardo B. Espiritu said Friday that foreign
consultants were found to have abused the privilege accorded to
them by the government by importing luxury cars for their personal
interests.
</P>
<P>
He also said that foreign consultants were allowed to bring in
cars tax-free for their personal use while doing their consultancy
jobs in the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
However, the DOF discovered that these consultants had brought
in luxury cars which they later dispose for profits.
</P>
<P>
Under the DOF policy, only service vehicles should be brought
in as part of their convenience during the duration of their stay
in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
