<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Interview: UNICEF to Enhance Cooperation with China (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China and the UNICEF have conducted six rounds of cooperation
since 1979 and up to now UNICEF has provided China with 230
million U.S. dollars of support and launched more than 150
projects focused on children's health and education and aid for
the handicapped.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Chinese government has donated 13 million U.S.
dollars to UNICEF.
</P>
<P>
Bellamy described China's use of UNICEF assistance as "a good
job", and noted that China is a member of the UNICEF governing
board, stressing that the relationship between China and UNICEF is
strong, both in activities throughout the country and in its
cooperation with the UNICEF governing board.
</P>
<P>
Talking about further funds UNICEF intends to offer China,
Bellamy said that UNICEF intends to increase overall resources if
this can be organized.
</P>
<P>
"This year we will provide 250,000 U.S. dollars for hygiene
projects in China in addition to the money we have already
allocated," she said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
