<HEADLINE> Part of Shenyang-Shanhaiguan Expressway to Open for Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 24 (Xinhua) -- A 170-kilometer-long section of
an expressway linking the capital city of northeast China's
Liaoning Province with Shanhaiguan in north China's Hebei Province,
will open for service in September this year.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the road surface, service facilities and a
greening project has been completed on the Jinzhou-Shanhaiguan
section of Shenyang-Shanhaiguan expressway, a local source said.
</P>
<P>
The entire line, with a length of 361 kilometers, will be put
into operation next year.
</P>
<P>
The line will be linked with Shenyang-Siping expressway,
forming an important passage from north to south, to alleviate the
transport "bottleneck" in the northeastern part of China.
</P>
<P>
At present, the province has 707 kilometers of expressways.
Liaoning will invest nearly 10 billion yuan into highway
construction this year, local authorities said.  
</P>
