<HEADLINE> Bomb Explodes Near British, U.S. Consulates in Central Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 24 (Xinhua) -- A home-made explosive device
blasted in the small hours Saturday near a building housing the
British and U.S. consulates in downtown Ekaterinburg in Russia's
central Urals region, ITAR-TASS reported.
</P>
<P>
The explosion, occurring at a parking lot, blew out windows in
the surrounding buildings but caused no casualties, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
Security agents soon arrived at the scene to investigate the
incident, seen by many as a retaliation to NATO airstrikes against
Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The explosion is the second of its kind after a gun-shooting
attack at the U.S. embassy in central Moscow on March 28. 
</P>
</TEXT>
