<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukrainian Parliament: Uphold Non-alignment Position </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian parliament on Thursday
strongly criticized NATO airstrikes against Yugoslavia and urged
the authorities to uphold the position of non-alignment.
</P>
<P>
NATO's attempt to expand its military action to territories
outside its members without authorization from the U.N. Security
Council was "very dangerous," added the parliament in a resolution
passed on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The parliament urged the president to strengthen his mediation
efforts over the Balkan conflict and the U.N. to hold an
international peace and security meeting on the issue in the city
of Kiev.
</P>
<P>
It also asked all parliamentary councils and government
departments to stick to the non-alignment policy and firmly
safeguard national interests under the constitution. Ukraine could
cooperate with global and regional security systems, but not join
any military and political alliance, it said.
</P>
<P>
Since NATO's actions were "aggressive in nature," it demanded,
Ukraine's relations with NATO should be re-examined.
</P>
<P>
Regarding European integrity as its strategic diplomatic target,
Ukraine has expanded cooperation with NATO since they forged a
special partnership in 1996. But their relationship was impaired
lately by NATO's savage bombing against Yugoslavia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
