<HEADLINE> 46 Die in Mexico Truck Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 23 (Xinhua)-- At least 46 people died in a
truck crash in southern Mexico Friday, the Chiapas state governor
Roberto Albores said in a tv interview.
</P>
<P>
The ill-fated flatbed truck carrying more than 50 people
plunged into a ravine near the town of Amatenango close to the
Guatemalan border northeast of Tapachula.
</P>
<P>
Independent TV Azteca said half of the dead were children,
without giving details.
</P>
<P>
The official Notimex news agency quoted police as blaming the
accident on a mechanical fault. 
</P>
