<HEADLINE> Moderate Quake Jolts Nicaragua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.4
degree on the open-ended Richter scale shook Nicaragua Friday
morning, the Territorial Studies Nicaraguan Institute (INETER)
told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The tremor occurred at 04:18 local time and its epicenter was
located 141 kilometers southwest of Managua.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter was in the Pacific Ocean, near La Boquita and
Casares, at a depth of eight kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The phenomenon was caused by the movements between the Cocos
and Caribbean tectonic plates, said INETER. 
</P>
</TEXT>
