<HEADLINE> Colombian Government to Maintain Dialog With ELN </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Colombian
government "will not close the door to dialogues" with the
National Liberation Army (ELN) which still holds hostages taken in
an air hijack, Colombia's High Commissioner for Peace Victor
Ricardo said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Ricardo said this is not the time to aggravate the disputes
between the government and the ELN.
</P>
<P>
He said if the ELN releases all the hostages, the government
will keep the proposals it made in the negotiations in February.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month the ELN hijacked a commercial passenger
plane, forcing it to land in a swamp-and-jungle region with all
passengers aboard taken hostage. Thirty-two people are estimated
to be kept in custody.
</P>
<P>
The government and the ELN representatives held two rounds of
talks on February 5 and 15 about the conditions to be offered by
the government for a national meeting.
</P>
<P>
The guerrillas have demanded demilitarization of four
municipalities in the Colombian northern part. 
</P>
</TEXT>
