<HEADLINE> Chile, Spain, Britain to Subject Pinochet Case to Arbitration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The arbitration will be held during the International
Convention Against Torture, signed by the three countries in 1988,
said Insulza in a press conference.
</P>
<P>
Chile will seek a ruling by the International Court of the
Hague, if no agreement is reached for such an arbitration, Insulza
said.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean government has been making efforts for Pinochet's
release, saying foreign courts do not have the right to try a
Chilean citizen for crimes allegedly committed in Chile.
</P>
<P>
The 83-year-old Pinochet, a lifetime senator, was detained in
London on October 16, 1998, at the request of Spanish Judge
Baltasar Garzon, who requested his extradition under charges of
human rights abuses committed during his rule. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
