<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Oil Basket Prices Increase This Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Venezuelan oil basket prices
increased this week by 0.98 dollars to 14.07 per barrel, the
Energy and Mines Ministry announced on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry attributed the rise to NATO's bombing in
Yugoslavia, a cut in world production caused by operational
problems in the North Sea and the explosion of a gas pipeline in
Venezuela's Monagas state.
</P>
<P>
Problems in the U.S. refineries were another factor for the
price rise.
</P>
<P>
The Venezuelan oil basket average price was 10.57 dollars per
barrel at the close of 1998, far below the 16.32 dollars average
registered in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The average price has had a noticeable recovery so far this
month to 13.35 dollars per barrel, against 8.43 dollars registered
February.
</P>
<P>
The oil basket price dropped 5.75 dollars per barrel in 1998,
causing a reduction of 43.5 percent (six billion dollars) in the
government income. 
</P>
</TEXT>
