it would petition for a nationally-legislated 100 pesos (about 2.5
U.S. dollars) increase in the minimum wage, calling it a "just and
urgent demand" for the continued survival of workers' families.
</P>
<P>
Caltex Philippines, Pilipinas Shell and Petron, the three
biggest oil companies of the country, have raised prices of fuel
products this week by an average of 43 centavos (1.075 U.S. cents)
to 50 centavos (1.25 cents) per liter.
</P>
<P>
The oil firms said they raised the prices only after the
Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries decided to cut back
its production to raise prices of crude oil in the world market.
