<HEADLINE> Finland to Take 1,000 Kosovo Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Finland has agreed to take 1,000
ethnic Albanian refugees from Kosovo in the coming two weeks in
reply to requests of the United Nations High Commission of
Refugees, the Labor Ministry announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
Labor Minister Sinikka Monkare told journalists here Friday
that the first 500 refugees, who will arrive early next week, will
be settled in refugee centers across the country. The rest 500
refugees are expected to arrive in two weeks.
</P>
<P>
These refugees, who came from Macedonian refugee camps, are
mostly ailing old people and children.
</P>
<P>
Monkare said that the refugees are supposed to stay in Finland
for half a year and, if the Kosovo war were not to end by that
time, they would be allowed to stay longer, but no more than three
years.
</P>
<P>
She added that Finland is ready to take more refugees if
necessary. Finland has the capacity to accommodate 6,000 to 10,000
refugees. 
</P>
