<HEADLINE> Big Money Staked at African Champions Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRAZZAVILLE, April 24 (Xinhua) -- African soccer clubs can cash
in big money from their Clubs Champions competitions while the
other two soccer tournaments have only modest bonuses at stake.
</P>
<P>
According to a report issued by the African Football Federation,
the African clubs can receive 6 million African francs (some 10,
000 US dollars) from every win, 3.5 million francs (some 6,000
dollars) from every draw and 600,000 francs (1,000 dollars) from a
single goal in the Champions tournament.
</P>
<P>
All the bonus were provided by the African Football Federation.
</P>
<P>
However, the Cup Winners' Cup and the Cup of the Confederation
of the African Football, were in short of the cash and the African
clubs can seldom balance their accounts in the competitions, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Mimosas of Abidjan won the Clubs Championship for a
total of 400 million African francs (some 690,000 US dollars),
including 13.8 million francs (24,000 dollars) for their 23 goals
scored in the tournament, and 80 million francs (138,000 dollars)
from the finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
