<HEADLINE> Thailand, Uzbekistan sign Agreement on Taxation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Thailand and Uzbekistan signed
here on Friday an agreement on the exemption of double taxation to
promote more cooperation in trade and investment.
</P>
<P>
The signing ceremony was jointly presided over by Thai Deputy
Foreign Minister Sukhumbhand Paribatra and his Uzbek counterpart
Adkham Bekmuradov, according to a Foreign Ministry's press
statement available Saturday.
</P>
