<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NATO to Provide Bulgaria With Security: Solana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- NATO will respond to possible
challenge coming from Yugoslavia to Bulgaria's security, which may
be triggered by its use of Bulgarian airspace.
</P>
<P>
This was stated by NATO Secretary General Javier Solana quoted
by the government Information Service Friday.
</P>
<P>
In a letter conveyed to Prime Minister Ivan Kostov by Deputy
Foreign Minister Konstantin Dimitrov, who negotiated on NATO's use
of Bulgarian sky, Solana said this is a follow-up of the position
voiced in his letter to Bulgarian President Peter Stoyanov on
April 20.
</P>
<P>
He said the security of NATO members is closely connected with
that of all partner-countries in Europe.
</P>
<P>
Since the security of the partner-countries is an immediate and
major concern of NATO, a threat by Yugoslavia to Bulgaria's
territorial integrity, political independence and security would
be unacceptable, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
