<HEADLINE> South African to Walk along the Equator Alone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Mike Horn hopes to become the
first man to walk along the equator, starting from May, the South
African said in a media conference here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Switzerland-living adventurer schedules to set off in May
from Gabon, sailing through the Atlantic alone for Brazil, walk
through the South American before crossing the Pacific and the
Indian Ocean to back to Africa.
</P>
<P>
Horn hopes to cover the 40,000 kilometer course in 17 months,
with three fourths in the sea, and another 10,000 kilometers on
the land which cross Gabon, Brazil, Ecuador, Colombia, Indonesia,
Somali, Kenya and Congo (K).
</P>
<P>
In order to tune up for his epoch-making adventure, Horn had
spent the last year along the Amazon River. 
</P>
</TEXT>
