<HEADLINE> Yellow Croaker Fry Bound for Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Some 300,000 large yellow
croaker fry are to be released into the East China Sea this summer,
in addition to the 150,000 released last year in a bid to
repopulate the fishing stocks.
</P>
<P>
It is part of a project introduced by Zhejiang province which
will also release whitebait, prawns and other aquatic species into
seas and lakes this year in an effort to develop a sustainable
local fishery industry.
</P>
<P>
As much as two million yuan will be spent on the project.
</P>
<P>
In the past 10 years, the province has been engaged in the
artificial breeding of such fish and then releasing the fries into
the sea. 
</P>
