<HEADLINE> Rebels Kill 371 Civilians in Colombia in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- A total of 371
civilians were killed by Colombian guerrillas and paramilitary
groups in the first three months of this year, the Colombian Army
said in a statement on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The army accused the guerrilla and paramilitary groups of
unleashing "a war of extermination" and of being the worst
violators of human rights.
</P>
<P>
It said that the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC)
killed 149 persons; the National Liberation Army (ELN) killed 22
and the Self-Defense paramilitary forces killed 179.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that in none of the cases the victims "had
anything to do with combats or any other kind of confrontations."
</P>
<P>
The FARC, as well as the ELN are trying to discuss a peace
agreement with the government. They will meet Saturday for the
second time in less than one week to try to resume peace
negotiations. 
