<HEADLINE> General History of China Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- All 12 volumes of the General
History of China have now been published by the Shanghai People's
Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
This book series relate the comprehensive history of the
world's most populous country from remote antiquity until 1949,
when the People's Republic of China was founded.
</P>
<P>
A major national project, the book series took more than 500
historians and archeologists some 20 years to complete.
</P>
<P>
Scholars say these volumes are currently the most comprehensive
and authentic work on Chinese history.
</P>
<P>
Many say the second volume, titled Remote Antiquity, is
especially valuable for its full and clear descriptions of ethnic,
cultural and social development in prehistoric China.  
</P>
