<HEADLINE> CAF Issues Bonds for 300 Million Euros </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Andean Development Corporation (
CAF) floated its first issue of bonds for 300 million euros in the
London and Frankfurt markets, with the most competitive interest
rate ever issued by a Latin American bond company.
</P>
<P>
A CAF publication says that this issue in euros seeks to
continue the financial diversification strategy aimed at boosting
investments in Europe.
</P>
<P>
The issue in euros has a five year maturity and 4.75 percent
interest.
</P>
<P>
This is the eighth issue of the kind made by CAF, and it has
already put in the market 1.2 billion U.S. dollars, as reported by
the corporation.
</P>
<P>
The CAF made its first bond emission in 1993 in the European
market and it has got received resources in these six years for 3
billion dollars, which have been distributed among the 12 Latin
American and Caribbean partners of this organization.
</P>
<P>
The CAF is made up of the five Andean Community countries,
namely Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador, Peru, and Venezuela, as well as
Brazil, Chile, Mexico, Panama, Paraguay, Jamaica, and Trinidad and
Tobago. 
