</P>
<P>
NEW YORK -- The Dow Jones industrial average fell Friday as
investors took profits after a three day rally.
</P>
<P>
The Dow closed down 37.51 at 10,689.67. The blue chip stocks
rose 286.65 points in the past three days and investors sell
stocks today to lock in their gains.(Dow Jones-Investors)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- Albanian Health Minister Leonard Soli said Friday
that the health situation of the Kosovo refugees in Albania is
under control.
</P>
<P>
He told a press conference that the problems of food,
accommodation, water and other items all have contributed to
health problems among the refugees, the number of which has risen
to 362,500 by Friday.
</P>
<P>
But thanks to measures adopted by the Albanian government,
Soli said, it is now under control.(Kosovo-Health)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The International Monetary Fund (IMF) and World
Bank will take actions to strengthen the Heavily Indebted Poor
Countries (HIPC) Initiative, a senior IMF official said here
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Tony Boote, in charge of the initiative at the IMF, said the
debt relief program for the world's most debt-ridden countries has
failed to live up to expectations and needs much work.(IMF-World
Bank) 
</P>
