<HEADLINE> Telephone Communication Improves in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The total number of telephone
lines operating in Myanmar has so far reached 225,164, increasing
by 158,457 as compared with the 1988 figure of 66,707, said the
latest issue of Myanmar Business News.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the total number of telephone exchange
stations has reached 523.
</P>
<P>
In the area of Yangon, Myanmar's capital, the number of the
telephone lines increased to 99,396 from 34,000 in 1988. The
number of the telephone exchange stations has reached 24.
</P>
<P>
To promote its telecommunication services, the concerned
authorities has extended its microwave links introduced in 1995,
enabling the capital to connect with nine other cities through the
system.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, CDMA mobile telephone system has an initial 3,000
lines in operation since its introduction in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, E-mail is also being used and internet service
provider being installed in the country. 
</P>
