<HEADLINE> World Bank Concerned Over Western Economic Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank (WB) is
concerned about the risk existing in the western economies, a
senior WB official said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Uri Dadush, director of WB Development Outlook Group, told a
seminar on the world economy outlook that the WB has a cautious
optimism about the world economy recovery due to the improvement
in southeast Asia and Brazil.
</P>
<P>
He said that the biggest danger in the short term could occur
in the industrialized countries.
</P>
<P>
The high level of the United States stock market and the
overvaluation of the dollar also cause concern to the WB.
</P>
<P>
World Bank representative in Brazil Suman Bery said that the WB
has no reservations that the measures adopted by the Brazilian
government will be beneficial, in the medium term, for the
economic stability and the sustainable growth of the South
American country. 
