<HEADLINE> Regional IT Forum Held in Xi'an </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The First China IT Regional Co-
operation and Development Forum, a nationwide promotion event
aimed at speeding up the development of information technology (IT)
in China, ended Friday in Xi'an, capital of Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day forum, more than 300 Chinese officials and
businessmen discussed regional economic development and its link
with IT, the importance of the development of the electronic
community for the future of IT, the necessity of regional co-
operation with foreign counterparts and regional market
construction for IT producers and sellers, according to today's "
China Daily".
</P>
<P>
"The uneven economic development throughout regions in China
requires regional co-operation that can break regional barriers
and promote exchange," said Chen Chong, deputy director of the
Electronic Information Product Administrative Department (EIPAD)
of the Information Industry Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Chen believes that the IT industry will expand in the next
century in China and play a vanguard role in regional co-operation.
</P>
<P>
Co-sponsored by the EIPAD and the Xi'an High-Tech Industry
Development Zone, the forum attracted a large number of IT
producers from home and abroad, such as China's Legend, Founder,
Dawncom, as well as overseas IBM, Hewlett Packard, and Compaq.
