<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Suspension Confirmed for Man United Duo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Manchester United players Roy
Keane and Paul Scholes have had their hopes of a Champions' Cup
reprieve quashed by European football governing body UEFA.
</P>
<P>
They were booked in the semi-final victory over Juventus and
the resulting bans rule them out of the final next month.
</P>
<P>
United had hoped they may be spared, but Uefa president,
Lennart Johansson, said Friday: "Although the English public might
want them to play, it would not be fair on the German team and the
bookings must stand."
</P>
<P>
United have been given some good news, however, after UEFA
spokesman Frits Ahlstrom announced that the club may receive more
tickets for the final.
</P>
<P>
It was believed that United and Bayern would receive only 25,
000 tickets each for the clash, despite the Nou Camp having a
capacity in excess of 110,000.
</P>
<P>
But Ahlstrom said: "The priority will be to benefit the two
teams that have qualified for a match in a stadium which will have
a capacity of 98,000 for this game." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
