<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chelsea Manager: Our Season is Over </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 23 (Xinhua) -- English Premier League football
club Chelsea manager Gianluca Vialli has admitted his side are now
likely to end the season empty handed after they failed to reach
the final of the Cup Winners' Cup.
</P>
<P>
The Blues, who won the trophy against Stuttgart in Stockholm
last year, were defeated 2-1 on aggregate by a single strike from
Real Mallorca's Argentinian star Leo Biagini on Thursday,
according to Friday's local reports.
</P>
<P>
Vialli was quoted as saying: "The future is bright for us
despite this disappointment.
</P>
<P>
"We probably won't win anything this season now but we are
still in a good position in the league and have reached the semi-
final in Europe. It is not a bad record and we are improving all
the time.
</P>
<P>
"You learn in life as you go along and if we want to become a
great side we must live with defeats like this as well as the
victories we are more used to.
</P>
<P>
"On another day we will have that luck and every side needs
that even when they are the best," he added.
</P>
<P>
Chelsea are now trailing third in the Premiership behind
Manchester United and Arsenal after last Sunday's 2-2 home draw
with Leicester in which they threw away a two goal lead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
