<DOCNO> XIE19990424.0254 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Falls After Three Day Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 23 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial average
fell Friday as investors took profits after a three day rally.
</P>
<P>
The Dow closed down 37.51 at 10,689.67. The blue chip stocks
rose 286.65 points in the past three days and investors sell
stocks today to lock in their gains.
</P>
<P>
Investors' concerns about AT&AMP;T's future also gave negative
impact on the Dow index. The telecommunication giant, a Dow
component, made a bid Thursday to buy MediaOne Group for about 58
billion U.S dollars after completing its acquisition of cable
company Tele-Communications Inc. last month.
</P>
<P>
Investors worried that the new bid could hurt AT&AMP;T's earnings
and that worries helped to pull the index down.
</P>
<P>
But the technology heavy Nasdaq index rose 29.08 to 2,590.69 as
Gateway 2000 reported strong earnings. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
index rose 1.97 to 1,356.85.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index fell 1.67 to 639.30. But the American
Stock Exchange composite index rose 11.98 to 770.36 and the
Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 2.97 to 431.82.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by 1,545 to 1,410 on the
New York Stock Exchange with 580 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 741.48 million shares from 918.36
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
