<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Health Situation of Kosovo Refugees Under Control: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 23 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Health Minister Leonard
Soli said Friday that the health situation of the Kosovo refugees
in Albania is under control.
</P>
<P>
He told a press conference that the problems of food,
accommodation, water and other items all have contributed to
health problems among the refugees, the number of which has risen
to 362,500 by Friday.
</P>
<P>
But thanks to measures adopted by the Albanian government, Soli
said, it is now under control.
</P>
<P>
The health sector in the country has paid a special attention
to the health problems among the Kosovo refugees and a doctor is
posted at each refugee camp to take care of the refugees, the
health minister said.
</P>
<P>
Non-governmental organizations have helped in coordinating,
controlling and planning the delivery of humanitarian aid from the
international community, he said.
</P>
<P>
Doctors at a refugee center in Tirana said that the most
serious problem is the shortage of medicines.
</P>
<P>
About 300 refugees fell ill on Wednesday in the center and most
of them suffered from cold and diarrhoea, the doctors said.
</P>
<P>
In the meanwhile, Kosovo refugees continued to enter Albania
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Albanian Information Minister Musa Ulqini said that 175 Kosovo
refugees crossed the border from the Morina point and 700 others
from the Hani Hotit point by 15:00 local time (1300 GMT) Friday.
</P>
<P>
"Referring to the situation on the northern border of Albania,
it has been calm today until 3 p.m. with no provocation or
incident reported, " Ulqini said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
